          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The family of entities having 1 required components each.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    },
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "discussion",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Discussion",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A family is a collection of entities with uniform component types per entity.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Entities that are be part of this family will have at least the 1 required components,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "but may have more components assigned.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A family is just a view on (component) data, creating them is cheap.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Use them to iterate efficiently over entities with the same components assigned.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Families with the same requirements provide a view on the same collection of entities (aka members).",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "A family conforms to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "LazySequenceProtocol",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and therefore can be accessed like any other (lazy) sequence.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "General usage",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "let family = nexus.family(requires: Comp1.self)",
            "\/\/ iterate each entity's components",
            "family.forEach { (comp1) in",
            "  ...",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Caveats",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Component types must be unique per family",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
